<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">Abstract &ndash;</span></span></strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;This report performs statistical analysis on the PUBG player performance dataset released by Kaggle in 2018. Key insights into the data were identified before employing the CatBoost model for regression to predict match outcomes. Each player&rsquo;s ranking at the end of a match is forecasted with high accuracy, achieving an RMSE of 0.08 and an R&sup2; score close to 1. The prediction model&apos;s performance is discussed in detail, and key findings from the analysis are highlighted.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>

                                    </li>

<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <ol start="1" style="list-style-type: decimal;color: transparent;">
        <li style="color: transparent;font-size: 21pt;">
            <p style="text-align: center;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 21pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">Introduction</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 21pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
        </li>
    </ol>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">To</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;understand the signiﬁcance of PUBG, one must be familiar with the idea of a &rsquo;battle royale&rsquo; game. &rsquo;Battle royale&rsquo; is a concept originating from a novel by Takami published in 1999 that was adapted into a ﬁlm in the following year. It refers to combat between a large number of individuals or teams where the objective is to eliminate all others and become the only player or team left. The movie was controversial, but overall received well in Japan, inspiring other movies, writ-ing and manga.&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;">However,</span><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;it is the gaming community that has strongly embraced the concept due to the deep sense of immersion that video games allow working extremely well in a competitive battle royale setting.</span><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;a virtual arena where up to 100 players engage in fierce combat. The objective? Be the last one standing. Think of it as a digital Hunger Games, minus the dystopian future.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">In a PUBG game, up to 100 players start in each match (</span><span style="color: transparent;border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;">matchId</span><span style="color: transparent;">). Players can be on teams (</span><span style="color: transparent;border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;">groupId</span><span style="color: transparent;">) which get ranked at the end of the game (</span><span style="color: transparent;">winPlacePerc</span><span style="color: transparent;">) based on how many other teams are still alive when they are eliminated. In game, players can pick up different munitions, revive downed-but-not-out (knocked) teammates, drive vehicles, swim, run, shoot, and experience all of the consequences -- such as falling too far or running themselves over and eliminating themselves.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">Origins:&nbsp;</span></span></strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">Brendan &ldquo;</span><span style="color: transparent;">PlayerUnknown</span><span style="color: transparent;">&rdquo; Greene birthed PUBG from an Arma 3 mod. The name? A blend of his nickname and the Japanese film &ldquo;Battle Royale.&rdquo;</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">Steam Sensation:</span></span></strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;PUBG stormed onto Steam in 2017, selling over 15 million copies during early access. It even set a record with one million simultaneous players!</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">Influence:</span></span></strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;PUBG&rsquo;s success spawned countless battle royale games. It&rsquo;s the trendsetter at the gaming party.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <ol start="2" style="list-style-type: decimal;color: transparent;">
        <li style="color: transparent;font-size: 21pt;">
            <p style="text-align: center;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 21pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">Game Mechanics</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 21pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
        </li>
    </ol>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">The key components of a game of PUBG are:</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <ul style="list-style-type: disc;color: transparent;">
        <li style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">
            <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">The Map:</span></span></strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;Four unique maps are available as of writing this report. Each map has a mixture of terrains with key settlements/towns that tend to have a higher con-centration of weapons, items and thus players.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <ul style="list-style-type: disc;color: transparent;">
        <li style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">
            <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">Weapons &amp; Items:</span></span></strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;A wide array of weapons, healing items and boosts are scattered around the map in a semi-random distribution. Weapons are more&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;">concentrated</span><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;around certain locations on each map.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <ul style="list-style-type: disc;color: transparent;">
        <li style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">
            <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">Vehicles:&nbsp;</span></span></strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">A wide array of drivable land and sea vehicles are available. Each player has a limited number of slots for weapons and items; although ﬁnding &rsquo;bag&rsquo; items like backpacks and allow players to increase inventory size.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <ul style="list-style-type: disc;color: transparent;">
        <li style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">
            <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">The Players:</span></span></strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;Up to 100 players are deployed per match, either solo or in teams of 2, 3 or 4.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <ul style="list-style-type: disc;color: transparent;">
        <li style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">
            <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">The&nbsp;</span></span></strong><span style="color: transparent;">Playzone</span><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;(The Circle):</span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;The main driving force of a PUBG match. This is a random circular area of the map that players must remain in. If outside the circle, players take damage and eventually die. The&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;">playzone</span><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;shrinks in 8 stages, each stage is faster and more damaging than the previous. Before the actual playzone (</span><span style="color: transparent;">represented</span><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;by a blue circle) shrinks, a white circle on the map shows players where the next playzone will be. Each circle representing the new&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;">playzone</span><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;is randomly generated.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">A standard PUBG match begins with up to 100 players joining a lobby. The players are then transported in a plane that travels in a randomly generated straight line across an island. Players can choose to exit the plane and parachute down to the surface of the map at any point; if any player does not jump out, they are automatically ejected from the plane at the far boundary of the map.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">Upon leaving the plane, players do not have any items or weapons; just their bare hands for combat. Thus, selecting where to land at the start of the match is a crucial. Some</span><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;">players/teams tend to avoid certain settlements, as they tend to have a higher concentration of weapons and players; thus, avoiding a highly competitive and dangerous initial few minutes. Some are more aggressive and prefer to race to these locations in search of better loot. They often have to engage opponents immediately; this is called &rsquo;hot drop-ping&rsquo;.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">Once on the ground, the initial priority is to scavenge for weapons and amour whilst getting an idea of where enemy players might be and where the playzone is shrinking to. The playzone begins with a very large circle; diameter of around 4500m. Players are shown the next stage; around 3000m with a white circle, before the actual zone begins to shrink. This repeats with smaller and smaller&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;">playzones</span><span style="color: transparent;">, the smallest being just 46.4m, until just one player or team is left.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">As the playzone gets smaller, players are forced to stay on the move. They are pushed into a more concentrated area, resulting in more encounters. Combat is mainly based around ﬁrearms, although hand-to-hand combat may also take place. Once a player takes sufﬁcient damage they may be &rsquo;downed&rsquo;;&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;">immobilized</span><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;until a team-mate revives them. If no revival takes place, or if a player is playing alone, they are &rsquo;killed&rsquo; and given their ranking according to how many players are left alive. They are not allowed to rejoin the match.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">Evidently there are countless strategies players can adopt, due to the wide variety of items and vehicles available, the vast and diverse maps as well as the unpredictability that comes with 100 competitive human players. For more information, Chris Carter from Polygon has an insightful article on the basic concepts and strategies of PUBG</span><span style="color: transparent;">.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <ol start="3" style="list-style-type: decimal;color: transparent;">
        <li style="color: transparent;font-size: 21pt;">
            <p style="text-align: center;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 21pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">Problem Statement</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 21pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
        </li>
    </ol>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">The objective of this project is to predict the performance of PUBG players based on their in-game statistics. By leveraging machine learning techniques, we aim to forecast a player&rsquo;s ranking at the end of a match. This can help in understanding the factors contributing to higher performance and strategizing gameplay for better results.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <ol start="4" style="list-style-type: decimal;color: transparent;">
        <li style="color: transparent;font-size: 21pt;">
            <p style="text-align: center;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 21pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">Data Description</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 21pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
        </li>
    </ol>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">Th</span><span style="color: transparent;">e</span><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;dat</span><span style="color: transparent;">aset</span><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;is provided with a large number of anonymized PUBG game stats of&nbsp;</span></span><strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">4</span></span></strong><span style="color: transparent;">.5 million</span><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">players</span><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;formatted so that each row contains one player&apos;s post-game stats.&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;">Each record is made up of 29 attributes that describe one player&rsquo;s statistics throughout one match.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">The following is a short description of the attributes used in this report:</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <ul style="list-style-type: disc;color: transparent;">
        <li style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">
            <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">DBNOs&nbsp;</span></span></strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">- Number of enemy players knocked.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <ul style="list-style-type: disc;color: transparent;">
        <li style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">
            <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">assists&nbsp;</span></span></strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">- Number of enemy players this player damaged that were killed by teammates.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <ul style="list-style-type: disc;color: transparent;">
        <li style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">
            <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">boosts&nbsp;</span></span></strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">- Number of boost items used.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <ul style="list-style-type: disc;color: transparent;">
        <li style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">
            <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;">damageDealt</span></span></strong><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">- Total damage dealt. Note:&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;">Self inflicted</span><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;damage is subtracted.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <ul style="list-style-type: disc;color: transparent;">
        <li style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">
            <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;">headshotKills</span></span></strong><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">- Number of enemy players killed with headshots.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <ul style="list-style-type: disc;color: transparent;">
        <li style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">
            <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">heals&nbsp;</span></span></strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">- Number of healing items used.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <ul style="list-style-type: disc;color: transparent;">
        <li style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">
            <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">Id&nbsp;</span></span></strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">- Player&rsquo;s Id</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <ul style="list-style-type: disc;color: transparent;">
        <li style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">
            <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;">killPlace</span></span></strong><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">- Ranking in match of number of enemy players killed.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <ul style="list-style-type: disc;color: transparent;">
        <li style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">
            <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;">killPoints</span></span></strong><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">- Kills-based external ranking of player. (Think of this as an Elo ranking where only kills matter.) If there is a value other than -1 in&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;">rankPoints</span><span style="color: transparent;">, then any 0 in&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;">killPoints</span><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;should be treated as a &ldquo;None&rdquo;.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <ul style="list-style-type: disc;color: transparent;">
        <li style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">
            <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;">killStreaks</span></span></strong><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">- Max number of enemy players killed in a short amount of time.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <ul style="list-style-type: disc;color: transparent;">
        <li style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">
            <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">kills&nbsp;</span></span></strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">- Number of enemy players killed.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <ul style="list-style-type: disc;color: transparent;">
        <li style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">
            <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;">longestKill</span></span></strong><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">- Longest distance between player and player killed at time of death. This may be misleading, as downing a player and driving away may lead to a large&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;">longestKill</span><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;stat.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <ul style="list-style-type: disc;color: transparent;">
        <li style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">
            <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;">matchDuration</span></span></strong><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">- Duration of match in seconds.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <ul style="list-style-type: disc;color: transparent;">
        <li style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">
            <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;">matchId</span></span></strong><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">- ID to identify match. There are no matches that are in both the training and testing set.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <ul style="list-style-type: disc;color: transparent;">
        <li style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">
            <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">matchType</span></span></strong><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">- String identifying the game mode that the data comes from. The standard modes are &ldquo;solo&rdquo;, &ldquo;duo&rdquo;, &ldquo;squad&rdquo;, &ldquo;solo-</span><span style="color: transparent;">fpp</span><span style="color: transparent;">&rdquo;, &ldquo;duo-</span><span style="color: transparent;">fpp</span><span style="color: transparent;">&rdquo;, and &ldquo;squad-</span><span style="color: transparent;">fpp</span><span style="color: transparent;">&rdquo;; other modes are from events or custom matches.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <ul style="list-style-type: disc;color: transparent;">
        <li style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">
            <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">rankPoints</span></span></strong><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">- Elo-like ranking of player. This ranking is inconsistent and is being deprecated in the API&rsquo;s next version, so use with caution. Value of -1 takes place of &ldquo;None&rdquo;.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <ul style="list-style-type: disc;color: transparent;">
        <li style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">
            <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">revives&nbsp;</span></span></strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">- Number of times this player revived teammates.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <ul style="list-style-type: disc;color: transparent;">
        <li style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">
            <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">rideDistance</span></span></strong><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">- Total distance traveled in vehicles measured in meters.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <ul style="list-style-type: disc;color: transparent;">
        <li style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">
            <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">roadKills</span></span></strong><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">- Number of kills while in a vehicle.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <ul style="list-style-type: disc;color: transparent;">
        <li style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">
            <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">swimDistance</span></span></strong><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">- Total distance traveled by swimming measured in meters.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <ul style="list-style-type: disc;color: transparent;">
        <li style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">
            <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">teamKills</span></span></strong><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">- Number of times this player killed a teammate.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <ul style="list-style-type: disc;color: transparent;">
        <li style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">
            <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">vehicleDestroys</span></span></strong><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">- Number of vehicles destroyed.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <ul style="list-style-type: disc;color: transparent;">
        <li style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">
            <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">walkDistance</span></span></strong><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">- Total distance traveled on foot measured in&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;">meters.-</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <ul style="list-style-type: disc;color: transparent;">
        <li style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">
            <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">weaponsAcquired</span></span></strong><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">- Number of weapons picked up.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <ul style="list-style-type: disc;color: transparent;">
        <li style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">
            <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">winPoints</span></span></strong><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">- Win-based external ranking of player. (Think of this as an Elo ranking where only winning matters.) If there is a value other than -1 in&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;">rankPoints</span><span style="color: transparent;">, then any 0 in&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;">winPoints</span><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;should be treated as a &ldquo;None&rdquo;.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <ul style="list-style-type: disc;color: transparent;">
        <li style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">
            <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">groupId</span></span></strong><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">- ID to identify a group within a match. If the same group of players plays in different matches, they will have a different&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;">groupId</span><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;each time.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <ul style="list-style-type: disc;color: transparent;">
        <li style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">
            <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">numGroups</span></span></strong><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">- Number of groups we have data for in the match.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <ul style="list-style-type: disc;color: transparent;">
        <li style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">
            <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">maxPlace</span></span></strong><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">- Worst placement we have data for in the match. This may not match with&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;">numGroups</span><span style="color: transparent;">, as sometimes the data skips over placements.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <ul style="list-style-type: disc;color: transparent;">
        <li style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">
            <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">winPlacePerc</span></span></strong><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">- The target of prediction. This is a percentile winning placement, where 1 corresponds to 1st place, and 0 corresponds to last place in the match. It is calculated off of&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;">maxPlace</span><span style="color: transparent;">, not&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;">numGroups</span><span style="color: transparent;">, so it is possible to have missing chunks in a match.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <ol start="5" style="list-style-type: decimal;color: transparent;">
        <li style="color: transparent;font-size: 21pt;">
            <p style="text-align: center;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 21pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">Project Methodolog</span><span style="color: transparent;">y</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 21pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
        </li>
    </ol>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: center;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;"><img src="data:image/png;base64," style="color: transparent; border: none;"></span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <ol start="6" style="list-style-type: decimal;color: transparent;">
        <li style="color: transparent;font-size: 21pt;">
            <p style="text-align: center;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 21pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">Data&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;">Wrangling</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 21pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
        </li>
    </ol>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 16pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">6.1&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;">Removing Null Values</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 16pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">The ﬁrst steps taken involve preprocessing the data in order to clean and better organize the records. Any null values not in essential attributes are identiﬁed using the NumPy &lsquo;</span></span><strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">.</span></span></strong><span style="color: transparent;">isnull</span><span style="color: transparent;">(</span><span style="color: transparent;">)</span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">&rsquo; function.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;"><img src="data:image/png;base64," style="color: transparent; border: none;"></span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">1 such instance was found</span></span></strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 16pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">6.2 Removing&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;">Instances</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 16pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 15pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">a.</span><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;">Kills&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;">wit</span><span style="color: transparent;">hout moving</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 15pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">Players spend between 1-3 minutes [16] at the start of each match parachuting down to the surface. This dataset does not capture the distance covered during this time, and thus, players who somehow get eliminated before landing, or land and fail to move at all have a&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;">totalDistance</span><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;of&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;">0.</span><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;">It is not possible to kill even 1 player if you do not move by&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;">atleast</span><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;1 unit. Following&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;">is</span><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;mostly used practices by cheaters (ones who interfere with the game&apos;s genuine natural processes):</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <ul style="list-style-type: disc;color: transparent;">
        <li style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">
            <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">Aimbots</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
        </li>

</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">6809 such instances were found</span></span></strong><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 16pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">6.3 Exploratory Data Analysis</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 16pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">There were finally 4436306 records picked out&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;">with 33 attributes for EDA.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;"><img src="data:image/png;base64," style="color: transparent; border: none;"></span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">No null values were found in the cleaned dataset.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: center;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;"><img src="data:image/png;base64," style="color: transparent; border: none;"></span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">T</span><span style="color: transparent;">o gain a better understanding of the correlations between attributes,&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;">we</span><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;generate a heatmap of r values. From the heatmap, as shown in the figure below, it appears that playersInMatch does not significantly correlate with the other attributes, which somewhat confirms the intuitive hypothesis.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;"><img src="data:image/png;base64," style="color: transparent; border: none;"></span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <ol start="7" style="list-style-type: decimal;color: transparent;">
        <li style="color: transparent;font-size: 21pt;">
            <p style="text-align: center;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 21pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">Feature Engineering</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 21pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
        </li>
    </ol>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">The provided dataset contained a large amount of data with a wide range of values.</span><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;Hence, new attributes are created from existing features</span><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;">in order to gain further insight into, better organise, and capture the different aspects of each player&rsquo;s performance.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">The maximum number of players in a match can be 100.</span><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;Some attributes for matches where 100 players have joined becomes 0 (100-100).</span><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;">Hence, when normalization is done for</span><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;such scenario using&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;">a normalization factor given below</span><span style="color: transparent;">:</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: center;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;"><img src="data:image/png;base64," style="color: transparent; border: none;"></span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">New attributes are created with this factor:</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;"><img src="data:image/png;base64," style="color: transparent; border: none;"></span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">To train the model effectively, it is wise to remove any unwanted columns before training our dataset. Hence, I have created a new data frame from the existing data frame to ensure that no data is l</span><span style="color: transparent;">ost, and&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;">also,</span><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;we do not train our model with excessive unwanted attributes.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: center;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;"><img src="data:image/png;base64," style="color: transparent; border: none;"></span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <ol start="8" style="list-style-type: decimal;color: transparent;">
        <li style="color: transparent;font-size: 21pt;">
            <p style="text-align: center;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 21pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">ML &ndash; Catboost Model</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 21pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
        </li>
    </ol>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">We</span><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;will have to train our model on varied categorical variables</span><span style="color: transparent;">. Columns like&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;">matchType</span><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;">are in form of labels but such data cannot be used to train models</span><span style="color: transparent;">,</span><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;in</span><span style="color: transparent;">cluding</span><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;CatBoost model</span><span style="color: transparent;">. Hence the data needs to be converted into numerical values</span><span style="color: transparent;">. For this,</span><span style="color: transparent;">&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;">I&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;">will use One</span><span style="color: transparent;">-</span><span style="color: transparent;">hot encoding</span><span style="color: transparent;">.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 16pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">8.1&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;">One-</span><span style="color: transparent;">H</span><span style="color: transparent;">ot Encoding</span><span style="color: transparent;">:</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 16pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: start;color: transparent;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 12px;">
    <p style="text-align: left;color: transparent;"><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: transparent;">One-hot Encoding is&nbsp;</span><span style="color: transparent;">used to convert categorical variables into a format that can be provided to machine learning algorithms to improve predictions. This method transforms categorical data into binary vectors, where each category is represented by a unique vector with all elements set to zero except the one corresponding to the category.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>

For instance, if the &quot;match type&quot; feature includes categories such as &quot;solo,&quot; &quot;duo,&quot; and &quot;squad,&quot; one-hot encoding creates separate binary columns for each type.</span></span><span style="color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
